          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          US-China trade talks
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/us-china-slash-tariffs-trade-war-deescalation-trump.png" alt="The United States and China have agreed to slash punitive tariffs against each other in a major de-escalation of Donald Trump’s trade war" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>The United States and China have agreed to slash punitive tariffs against each other in a major de-escalation of Donald Trump’s trade war. Credits: AP Photo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Trump announced “great progress” in trade talks with China and described a “total reset” in relations between the world’s two largest economies. His administration announced that “neither side is interested in decoupling.” For the next 90 days, the US will <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-12-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-cut-tariffs-on-chinese-imports?source=website" target="_blank">cut tariffs on Chinese imports</a> from 145 percent to 30 percent, while China will reduce them from 125 percent to 10 percent.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         China's Vice Premier He Lifeng said both sides agreed to establish a "China-US economic and trade consultation mechanism." He acknowledged the current talks were a “positive and necessary step” toward de-escalation. A joint statement is expected to be released today.</p>  
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
         On Truth Social, Trump said the negotiations were “<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-12-may-25-spotlight-h1-2-friendly-but-constructive?source=website" target="_blank">friendly but constructive.</a>” The US negotiating team claimed the agreement would bring down the massive trade deficit between the two sides. Analysts assert that the trade war is over and that America started something, and they couldn’t finish it. </p>  
        
        </mj-text>
